I think you need some more time before your character analysis of complete strangers holds up to the claims. there is a difference between being unaware that your godlike mechanics and game strategy actually has punishable flaws, vs trying to learn how to carry games and be the one and only person on your team willing to make shit happen and not farm mid all game long and mindlessly push waves until the 4 ff votes role through. 

the real arrogance in this situation lies within the person that thinks they shouldn't be punished so hard for making mistakes in the lane, and baby flames instead of changing something about the way they approach the matchup through the game.
{{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}

